  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "NVIDIA CUDA toolkit for all platforms contains a vulnerability in the cuobjdump binary, where a user could cause an out-of-bounds read by passing a malformed ELF file to cuobjdump. A successful exploit of this vulnerability might lead to a partial denial of service.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2024-53870 describes a software vulnerability in NVIDIA CUDA toolkit's cuobjdump binary (out-of-bounds read leading to possible DoS). The CUDA toolkit is a core software component used to build, train, deploy, and run AI workloads, making this a relevant AI supply-chain vulnerability in AI software stacks. The vulnerability is actionable as a CVE with details (CWE-125, CVSS 3.1)."
  },
